{"type": "article", "id": 39039, "title": "用纸板做的大楼，看起来就像真实的街景｜这个设计了不起", "description": "我们每天都为你推荐几个最近发现的好设计。", "date": "2017-03-21T23:21:50Z", "super_tag": "", "tags": [{"id": 271, "name": "工业设计"}, {"id": 8581, "name": "Peca"}, {"id": 38769, "name": "Colorware"}, {"id": 38770, "name": "Joshua Smith"}, {"id": 38771, "name": "Me Kyeoung Lee"}, {"id": 44013, "name": "Tronnovate"}], "category": 17, "column": 38, "author": 400262, "comment_count": 8, "praise_count": 135, "image": "img/article/article_show/20170321210740MQurop7lnZB9sRVv.jpg", "contents": "<p nocleanhtml=\"true\">        <style type=\"text/css\"> p.p1 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 27.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636} p.p2 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 27.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636; min-height: 25.0px} p.p3 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 32.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636} p.p4 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 32.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636; min-height: 25.0px} span.s1 {font-kerning: none} </style>  </p><p>「这个设计了不起」的微信公众号上线啦，直接搜索「BestDesign」或是「Qthings」就可以订阅，关注我们每日发现的新鲜好设计。</p><h3>23 Temple Street by Joshua Smith</h3><p>来自澳大利亚的 <a href=\"http://www.iknowjoshuasmith.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Joshua Smith</a> 是一名热衷于制作微型建筑模型的艺术家，这个取材于香港庙街 23 号的 1:20 大楼模型是他的最新作品。在用纤维板、硬纸板和塑料等材料完成框架之后，Smith 会用颜料和粉彩仔细地还原出店铺招牌、卷帘门上的涂鸦甚至房间里的海报这些细节——光看照片，你或许还会以为这是大楼的实景。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170321211005yh3mFCGtNTcoMqQf.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.184000\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170321211004XZTY3L6QwanJVmIC.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.188000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170321211004bYfJRNKdcxzUo1Sh.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170321211004fH0KeLNk6Qx8VvWj.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666500\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170321211006fKZA5zx4BvNU0gTF.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>iPhone 7 Plus Retro by Colorware</h3><p><a href=\"http://www.colorware.com/default.aspx\" rel=\"nofollow\">Colorware</a> 是美国一家专门对电子产品进行涂装改造的设计公司，这款模仿第一代 Macintosh 的复古版 iPhone 7 Plus 就是它的最新产品。有了淡黄配色、两侧条纹以及彩虹 logo 的加持，让手机拥有了一种神奇的穿越感。这些复古版都是基于 256G 的黑色 iPhone 7 Plus 所改造的，你可以通过<a href=\"http://www.colorware.com/p-744-colorware-iphone-7-plus-retro.aspx\" rel=\"nofollow\">官方网站</a>订购，售价为 1899 美元。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170321210834rJwqsoQgN1dPS684.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.500000\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170321210834clVEk7HF69DRYIL3.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.600244\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170321210834bZOv2dhySfBYHpuq.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.651589\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>FLATPAC by TRONNOVATE</h3><p>每次出门前，难免会因为整理行囊浪费不少时间。为了帮助人们更快地完成收纳，来自台湾的设计团队 <a href=\"https://www.tronnovate.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">TRONNOVATE</a> 推出了一款模仿布包裹的轻质背包 FLATPAC。它就像一块自带夹层和小口袋的布料，利用搭扣和拉链取代了传统的折叠方式，三秒内就能完成打包。灵活性是 FLATPAC 的另一个优势，无论是哪一种背法，你都可以从三个不同的方向拿取物品。这是它的<a href=\"https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/1820164289/flatpac-just-pack-and-unpack-in-a-second\" rel=\"nofollow\">众筹链接</a>，售价从 28 美元起。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170321210847SAdQ8tXIGrzJ7vNi.gif\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.556250\" data-format=\"gif\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170321210846qKiaMHQZc7rpz8IT.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666176\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170321210847F45UD6i9dBvKOJkC.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.566176\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170321210847BvSOLgKZ63qwmx09.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.627941\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Pita Daybed by Peca</h3><p>这张名为 Pita 的坐卧两用沙发是墨西哥设计工作室 <a href=\"http://www.peca.com.mx/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Peca</a> 的最新作品。橡木制框架的结构相当简洁，一部分还向上延伸为几何形的靠垫提供支撑。Pita 的名字来源于当地名为 piteado 的传统刺绣工艺，圆柱形皮革枕上那些像是细雨般的图案就是通过这种方式加工而成的。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170321210923CRWstBgSxYj2FEHi.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.653906\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170321210923kJEliUzTsrY8DbwM.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.748148\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/2017032121092480Fv1KmziqJPR9uQ.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.288889\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170321210927SQYroxOjJmi4kz6Z.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.500000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Frui by Bo Sun</h3><p>现居英国曼切斯特的设计师 <a href=\"https://www.behance.net/boreumsun\" rel=\"nofollow\">Bo Sun</a> 为独居人士构思了一个专门提供一人份水果的概念品牌 <a href=\"https://www.behance.net/gallery/15827189/Frui\" rel=\"nofollow\">Frui</a>。Sun 并没有选择常见的全封闭纸袋，而是通过卷起后自带提手的外包装完成打包，强调了轻便和健康的概念。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201703212110337JxXRQc6TSCslM2e.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.713333\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170321211034NJKxXY05fznWBtwj.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.670000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Corner Store Illustrations by Me Kyeoung Lee</h3><p>还记得小时侯买零食的街边小铺吗？在过去二十年的时间里，韩国艺术家 <a href=\"http://www.leemk.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Me Kyeoung Lee</a> 用柔和的笔触记录下了这些逐渐消失的店铺。这些充满人情味的作品都是她用丙烯酸颜料绘制的，为了避开阴影的干扰，她还会特意赶在午间完成素描。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201703212110570APvMwE5qgjK9uTO.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.846000\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170321211059DGB5YU2j06f9aiVm.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.648000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170321211056vpCTiY0fsjtZc634.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.855556\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/2017032121105671hp6ZG4bjlVzmKa.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.576000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170321211057mNkO4BKV2bP09woT.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.787000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170321211058qnePHJFiWVuSvRDk.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.222222\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div>"}